ofthemiscrya.showMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#cc9966 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#cc9966 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#993300>(9/20/00 11:19:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Hippolyte?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LABRYS Amazon Tavern... a phoenix rises</span><hr size=1> ::Hipp smiled as she stood beside Ariah and looked over the new tavern.  It had been a hard thing to do..burning the old one down.  But, it had needed to be cleansed of the negative energy that had built up within.  And now.. in it's place stood a new structure.  A tavern for the Themiscryans to meet those from the outside world.  The LABRYS had always stood far from the village of Themiscrya.  On the outer edge of Themiscryan lands, it was a well known place for a good time, spars, drinks, or a relaxing soak in the hot tub.  <br>
Today, had been a day of hot and hard work.  As Dawn, Ariah, Hippolyte, and other amazons labored to rebuild this well known tavern.  And like a phoenix it stood reborn.  Hipp looked to Ariah proud:: I think it looks even better then before!  ::chuckles:: all it needs now.. is a few spars!  I am sure the Themiscryans are up to that.  :: Ariah and Dawn chuckled over the Queen's words.  They all knew it would not take long for a spar to start up in the tavern, and for a chair to be broken.  Thank the Gods, there were some great carpenters in the tribe.  Hipp saluted the stucture:: May the Gods bless you, LABRYS.  And may you be home to all women...and a place for friends to meet!   <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
