Hours pass and still find her huddling against the tree..she watches.  She has seen a few men..and several women pass, going in and out of the tavern.  She has become curious at the site of that most of the women are dressed as warriors.  They remind her of the warrior named Livia who she fought against in Rome.  But, surely these could not be Romans.  Not this far.<br>
As the rain pounds down upon the tree above her..and then beats upon her..the almost thoroughly soaked woman watches still silent.  Having almost become one with the tree.  <br>
Then a figure dressed in purple and burgandy slip out of the tavern.  Ara stops her breath..watching.::: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A> at: 9/26/00 11:27:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#993300>(9/26/00 11:53:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> As the celebration moves into the night</span><hr size=1> :::Hippolyte stepped out of the tavern..and looked up at the heavens.  Cocking a brow, she smirked.  Endaksi, Zeus.. I think that is about enough for today..don't you? ::she then steps back inside the tavern..and grabs a leather cloak from the back wall.  Says her goodbyes again...and then wrapping herself up..she walks out to her mare. She smirks as the rain begins to slow to a spitting drizzle and chuckles:: Well..Zeus..you do listen to women after all..don't you?  :::  She then looks to her mare and just as she places her hands upon the saddle..she stops.  Her senses telling her she is being watched.  She slowely turns her head..scanning the edge of the forest that surrounds the LABRYS.  Knowing the every bend of the trees that surround the LABRYS, after all these years...her eyes notice that one tree..is a bit wider then usual.  Her hands pull off the saddle and one moves to her scimitar..resting her palm on the pammel beneath her cloak.  She begins a slow..deliberate walk towards the form.  Her eyes narrow..trying to see the form thru the rain::: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 9/26/00 12:47:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(9/26/00 12:04:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/arahutajiwarli?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: As the celebration moves into the night</span><hr size=1> ::: Ara watches as the figure moves towards her. By now, she has seen that this was one of the warrior women in the tavern.  She sighs and breathes a quiet deep breath.  Speaking to herself in her mind she says::: {Yhi, be with me} :::As the woman approaches...Ara moves out slowely from the tree. Pushing her hands out from her cloak.  She shows she has no weapon in her hands.  Her heart beating quickly.  Even though, Ara knew how to spar and fight with the best of them.  She sought and tried peaceful ways. In a soft voice she spoke a word she hoped this warrior knew.:::<br>
<br>
Peace <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A> at: 9/26/00 12:06:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#993300>(9/26/00 12:57:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Hippolyte?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: As the celebration moves into the night</span><hr size=1> ::The form moves out from under the tree to reveal a woman...about the same height as the Queen.  But, her skin much browner than any Hippolyte had seen before.  Her eyes were of a dark amber colour...with a peacefulness..even tho the face was wary.  The woman showed empty palms to Hipp...and then spoke the word Peace.  This was a word she had seldom heard in these lands.  The woman continued to stand before the Queen..her hands showing no weapons.  Hipp moved her hands out of her cloak..and a soft smile rose to her lips.::: Yasoo... I am Queen Hippolyte.   <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
